question_text: A water tank initially contains $500$ gallons of water. Water drains from the tank at a constant rate of $10$ gallons per minute. Which type of model is best to represent the amount of water remaining in the tank, in gallons, after $m$ minutes?

options.label: A linear model with a positive slope
A linear model with a negative slope

options.label: For all $x > 0$, it is true that $3^x < 3x+1$.
For all $x > 0$, it is true that $3^x > 3x+1$.
There is a constant $c$ such that if $0 < x < c$, then $3^x < 3x+1$, but if $x > c$, then $3^x > 3x+1$.
